Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.27,0:00:07.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Together with the Detective Boys, Ran and company, I boarded the Bell Tree Express...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.07,0:00:11.78,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The suspicious passengers gathered in Carriage 8...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:16.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The black shadow closing in on Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.83,0:00:24.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then, the deduction quiz taking place aboard the train unexpectedly turned into a sealed room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.96,0:02:36.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.00,0:02:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody shot this guy in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.72,0:02:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the door was chain-locked, and you had to break through the lock to get in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.81,0:02:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So wouldn't this be a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.98,0:02:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't figured out how the door was locked yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.56,0:02:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no burn mark around the gunshot wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.11,0:02:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That proves he was shot from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.07,0:03:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since if you were shooting yourself in the head, you'd have to hold the gun right next to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.32,0:03:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But maybe he got scared right before shooting, and pulled it away unintentionally?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.96,0:03:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.96,0:03:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a silencer attached to the gun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.96,0:03:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you really think it's possible to hold something that long at a distance from your head and still fire it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.34,0:03:25.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And look, on the sofa opposite, there's a mark from something like a gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.10,0:03:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer probably made the victim hold the gun and shoot an extra round,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.89,0:03:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to leave gunshot residue on their hand and sleeve, to make it look like suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.77,0:03:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, gunshot residue would've landed on the killer too,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but they probably washed it off their hands, and threw their clothes out of the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the killer must still be on this train. They won't get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you guys go back to your room with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.71,0:04:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we want to help out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.80,0:04:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be reckless!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.26,0:04:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until I come back, lock your room door and don't open it for anyone at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with you, all of a sudden...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're scary sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhh, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.52,0:04:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it dangerous since there's a murderer lurking around?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'm counting on you to take care of the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.78,0:04:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.28,0:04:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.11,0:04:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should call Dad and have him come here, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.28,0:04:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.49,0:04:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the commotion about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:33.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the deduction quiz already started!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.58,0:04:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, it's not the quiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.71,0:04:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a real murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:40.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An actual murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dreadful...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.55,0:04:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't deal with an actual murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too gory for my taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.13,0:04:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, stop the train and tell the passengers not to leave their rooms until the police arrive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.48,0:04:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I have your attention, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In light of an accident that just took place on the train,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we are considering changing our course and stopping at the nearest station.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.44,0:05:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We apologise for the inconvenience,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:11.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but please remain in your rooms until further notice, and refrain from leaving them if at all possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.45,0:05:15.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The ominous feeling I felt before hasn't gone away...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:18.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And his attitude back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.46,0:05:20.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What was that about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.39,0:05:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.64,0:05:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're on this train too, Amuro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.73,0:05:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I managed to get myself a ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just met Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} at the dining car, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran, who's the hot guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.99,0:05:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the detective I told you about the other day, the one who wanted to be Dad's apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.12,0:05:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you, I'm Sonoko Suzuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.75,0:06:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pleasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it seems some sort of accident happened. Do you know anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.59,0:06:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there's been a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sera{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} are still at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it might be wise to have Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} handle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.23,0:06:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears that the heavens are siding with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.11,0:06:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! You're not gonna stop until you reach Nagoya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.03,0:06:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I ask you to stop at the nearest station?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner of the train, Advisor Jirokichi Suzuki said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Tie the scurvy jackanapes who dared to kill a man in {\i1}my{\i0} train up and bring them here to me!'
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.83,0:06:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and so, he's waiting to ambush the killer at Nagoya...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:47.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just how much power does that geezer have?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.71,0:06:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we reach Nagoya Station, I, the great detective Poirō Mouri,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.72,0:07:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,shall unveil the truth of this murder on the Bell Tree Express for all to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.94,0:07:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed! I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Mr. Conductor,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when did you last see the victim, Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.82,0:07:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was in front of Room A, Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard the bell ring, so I went to Room A,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.79,0:07:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,only to be scolded by Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, saying he hadn't called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.58,0:07:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the same time, Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} opened the door of Room B and peeked out at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that really Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.63,0:07:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He seemed to be on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.05,0:07:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how about we ask Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about this, 'Poirō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.65,0:07:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I heard Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice from beyond the door as well back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.44,0:07:55.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Taisaku Noto (52)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room A
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.19,0:07:55.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I never thought he'd be next door, I was quite surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.99,0:08:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, why did you lie about having rung the bell and say you hadn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, I never rang the bell, the conductor came on his own!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.58,0:08:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when you ring the bell, the light above the door comes on, so I doubt he'd have made a mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.26,0:08:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, though the rest work, Room A's light is burnt out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.59,0:08:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when I heard a bell ring and didn't see any of the lights on,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.60,0:08:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it must've been Noto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s room, so I knocked on his door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:26.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.15,0:08:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just after the doors to rooms A and B shut, a bell rang,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.78,0:08:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw the light for Idenami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s room, Room E, was lit and went to check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.87,0:08:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.49,0:08:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}did{\i0} ring the bell to call the conductor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.74,0:08:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was hearing strange noises in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:49.54,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mari Idenami (33)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room E
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.66,0:08:46.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,They turned out to be this wristwatch's alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.67,0:08:49.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I found it stuck down the back of the sofa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.84,0:08:53.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must've been left behind by someone, maybe one of the cleaners.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.05,0:08:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you called to have the conductor search your room,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.51,0:09:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then that may be the time the killer entered the victim's room,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.47,0:09:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since the conductor wouldn't be watching over the passageway as usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Search my room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only called him here to complain!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found this thing myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't stand the thought of others invading my territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.86,0:09:23.91,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Then even though you were in the passageway the whole time, you didn't see anyone suspicious enter the victim's Room B, Mr. Conductor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.91,0:09:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was listening to Idenami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, the door to the room farthest to me opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.63,0:09:34.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I had the feeling somebody was peeping over here from beyond the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.76,0:09:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The farthest room from you would be Room A...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just before I spotted that suspicious person,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Komino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} was wheeled out of Room D by her maid and headed in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.98,0:09:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So those two might've seen something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.31,0:09:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Komino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.48,0:09:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Room A door?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:10:01.07,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Natsue Komino (75)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room D
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.61,0:10:01.07,Dialogue,,0,320,0,,That door wasn't open\Nwhen I passed by.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.07,0:10:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And of course, I didn't see anyone suspicious standing by the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:09.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Sumitomo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.42,0:10:16.72,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hiruka Sumitomo (37)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room D
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.08,0:10:16.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The only open door was the one to Room E, from which we heard Idenami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.88,0:10:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe it opened after Komino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} passed by...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:29.56,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,But we passed by the two ladies at the entrance to Carriage 8 when we were heading to Room B,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.56,0:10:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we didn't see the Room A door open either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.44,0:10:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did it really open?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.11,0:10:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.11,0:10:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just before the kids came over, Andō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} from Room C came over to check on things,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.62,0:10:52.58,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Satoru Andō (41)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room C
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:50.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I could hear Idenami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} shouting even in my room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:54.75,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,so I left my room to find out what was going on. I thought something might've happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.17,0:11:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I can't say whether the door to Room A was open or not, since I went in the opposite direction, to Room E.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.97,0:11:07.97,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Not to mention that at the time, the train was passing through a tunnel, so there wasn't any light shining through the windows,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.97,0:11:10.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the passageway was pretty dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.06,0:11:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, it was dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.69,0:11:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You arrived just after I left my room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we didn't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, you Carriage 8 passengers all seem to be quite sure of each other's names and rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.37,0:11:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.25,0:11:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We board the Mystery Train together every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.37,0:11:38.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're our regular guests who always make reservations in this first-class car before anybody else, every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.84,0:11:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they always choose the same rooms, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.26,0:11:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So basically...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.56,0:11:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Conductor, it was all in your imagination, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.85,0:11:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! I'm confident I saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.31,0:11:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, that's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.65,0:12:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one who secretly let the killer into Room B!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.36,0:12:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it was a sealed room, but there's actually some sort of hidden door leading to the next room, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing like that in this train!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you gathered all the passengers from rooms A, C, D and E into room B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they each fired a bullet into the victim's body, one by one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.38,0:12:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.71,0:12:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how I would've written it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.14,0:12:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the plot of Orient Express?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:34.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And for starters, the victim was only shot once in total...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.31,0:12:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sent it to the Mouri Detective Agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The footage from the camp trip last week?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. We want to properly thank the lady who saved us, so we figured a great detective might be able to find out who she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.00,0:12:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I watched that video along with Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.87,0:12:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said there's no way to find someone with just a face and voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:13:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but if we posted it online, maybe someone would recognise her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.30,0:13:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady had a Mystery Train Pass Ring,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we'd all been saying we might see her here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.89,0:13:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't seen her yet, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.68,0:13:12.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.56,0:13:16.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The reason for this ominous feeling in my chest...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:18.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.94,0:13:20.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me that {\i1}they{\i0}'ve...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:31.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Heed my command, troops!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:34.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Breach the train the moment it arrives,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:40.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,bind the confounded murderer hand and foot with lightning speed and bring them forth to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.00,0:13:42.13,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why won't you answer?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:48.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Advisor Suzuki, please stop giving my subordinates orders without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:50.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Allow us Aichi Police to handle this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.26,0:13:50.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.80,0:13:55.43,Thoughts,,10,10,0,,{\be10}bell tree
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.80,0:13:55.43,Dialogue Top,,10,10,0,,The train crowned with my surname, Suzuki, became a murder site!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.43,0:13:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You dare to tell me to just sit and wait, you fool?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:14:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon capturing the miscreant, hang high the head of our filthy quarry on the central tower of Nagoya Castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.53,0:14:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.40,0:14:09.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds like some sort of petty killing took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.20,0:14:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems fortune is smiling upon us, Bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.78,0:14:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.91,0:14:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's sending that iron snake right here non-stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.58,0:14:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I just heard from Vermouth. She confirmed that Sherry's aboard the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Vermouth and Bourbon will be dealing with her about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.97,0:14:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care whether they decided to ice or capture her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question was whether she was inside that snake's stomach or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.27,0:14:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you've already been swallowed by the snake, Sherry,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.23,0:14:44.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then Nagoya shall be your final stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.45,0:14:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.16,0:14:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the room of the deceased, Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was chain-locked shut,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.24,0:15:04.21,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,and our conductor here never left the passageway at the time, and he didn't see anyone suspicious entering or leaving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious it was a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there weren't any burn marks around the bullet wound in his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a gunshot mark on the sofa opposite, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.22,0:15:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everybody aboard this train's a mystery fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was planning to die, then he probably left red herrings to make it look like a murder, to make his death into a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.27,0:15:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.61,0:15:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really are the amazing Sleeping Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.07,0:15:34.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For today, please call me 'Poirō'!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.16,0:15:41.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, that Murobashi guy swapped rooms with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, and seemed really eager to help with the whole mystery quiz thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine somebody like that committing suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.83,0:15:48.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems the cue card for the mystery quiz was fake, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.67,0:15:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.34,0:15:59.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!\N\NYou've been selected to play\Nthe role of the detective!\NIn 10 minutes, an incident will\Ntake place in Carriage 7, Room B,\Nso please investigate!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.05,0:15:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though it looks like our usual cue cards, the contents don't match with the trick we were expecting...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.31,0:16:01.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I thought so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.64,0:16:06.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Somebody moved Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} to the first-class carriage for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.94,0:16:13.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was it because the old man took over the first-class Room B, which Murobashi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} usually reserved for himself...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.78,0:16:17.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means it's a trick that can only be done in this carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.74,0:16:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is there anything special about this carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.12,0:16:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything special?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rooms A to E always have the same people booking into them year after year, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.30,0:16:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Bell Tree Express was finished five years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.34,0:16:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I heard that this first class carriage was created on special request by a wealthy friend of Advisor Jirokichi Suzuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.10,0:16:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, that friend was a huge fan of the Orient Express,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the rooms in this carriage were made especially large so a family could comfortably fit in one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.94,0:16:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, are any of the passengers here part of that magnate's family?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.20,0:16:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Almost all of the family died in a large fire a month before the maiden trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.87,0:17:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only one member of the family is aboard...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.25,0:17:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Komino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} in Room D.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:11.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, she was the aunt of the magnate who died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That case is on the Internet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.55,0:17:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fire broke out during the magnate's birthday party, and said magnate's family died along with twelve other attendees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.81,0:17:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only survivors were Komino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was just mentioned, her maid Sumitomo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and four other attendees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.32,0:17:35.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could those four attendees now be the other passengers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of the fire was put down to a problem with an electric cable, but no clear reason was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.83,0:17:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If our murder here is a revenge drama connected to the fire in some way,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then this is looking more and more like the Murder on the Orient Express!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.75,0:17:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go talk to those passengers again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.71,0:18:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, speaking of electricity, why didn't you change the dead light bulb over Room A?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beyond the first-class carriage is the luggage car, and we usually keep spare bulbs there, but today we couldn't find any.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the people making all the final checks before departing are the conductors, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two or three of us go around the rooms, making sure the water works and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I heard a conductor's uniform went missing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You worried about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.90,0:18:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. I was looking at the article on the fire too, but haven't worked out anything yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.71,0:18:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our opponent's probably sweating, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.59,0:18:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since on a train running at 80 km/h, there's no way to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:53.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What should I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:55.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.57,0:19:01.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If the Organisation really have come for me, aboard this train...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.91,0:19:04.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:07.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't stay here anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.58,0:19:15.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An e-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:18.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I don't know the address...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.92,0:19:19.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.80,0:19:25.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}'Are you ready?'
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:27.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Vermouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.81,0:19:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.77,0:19:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got an e-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.86,0:19:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's it from?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.78,0:19:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it from Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.74,0:19:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.65,0:19:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just spam...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.24,0:19:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.16,0:19:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.25,0:19:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to take some medicine for my cold, so I might be a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.67,0:20:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave her alone, you'll just get on her nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.09,0:20:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But earlier, when we were coming back here, she was clinging onto the hem of my shirt the whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think she's worried about something...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.22,0:20:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I want to be by her side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.02,0:20:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:17.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.44,0:20:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:39.54,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Okay, so until your 19th birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.54,0:20:40.25,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}bye-bye...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:46.26,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, maybe it's about time I told you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:52.02,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The truth is, your mother's making a terrifying drug, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.47,0:20:56.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My lab mates are getting all hyped up about it, like it's a dream drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.27,0:21:00.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Your dad and I are putting our hopes on it and calling it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.27,0:21:04.78,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}'Silver Bullet'.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.40,0:21:13.91,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But to finish this drug, your dad and I will have to leave you and your sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.91,0:21:17.29,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please understand, Shiho.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.54,0:21:21.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm sorry, Mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.25,0:21:23.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I didn't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:27.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...that this drug was something that shouldn't be made...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:32.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But in order to avoid getting other people involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.64,0:21:35.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I have no choice but to rely on it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.99,0:21:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like your sister, I can read all your moves...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.25,0:22:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, would you step this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.38,0:22:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...into our area?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.84,0:22:09.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.84,0:22:11.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Not now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.39,0:22:15.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't be killed looking like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.49,0:23:49.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tools for the sealed room trick are in there, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.12,0:23:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister, can I record a video of you running?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.12,0:23:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your maid's quite fast when she runs. Did she use to play sports?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.25,0:24:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That wristwatch you found in your room...
